test_presence_of_duplicates_in_result:
assert (3 == 3 and 3 == 3 and 2 == 3)
 +  where 3 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x7e3b1bb8dcc0>([851])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x7e3b1bb8dcc0> = [[1, 851], [1, 851, 1], [851], [851, 1], [1, 851], [1, 851, 1], ...].count
 +  and   3 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x7e3b1bb8dcc0>([1, 851])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x7e3b1bb8dcc0> = [[1, 851], [1, 851, 1], [851], [851, 1], [1, 851], [1, 851, 1], ...].count
 +  and   2 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x7e3b1bb8dcc0>([851, 1])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x7e3b1bb8dcc0> = [[1, 851], [1, 851, 1], [851], [851, 1], [1, 851], [1, 851, 1], ...].count
test_if_sublist_product_equals_number:
assert 1 == 851
 +  where 1 = <built-in function prod>([])
 +    where <built-in function prod> = math.prod
